    <article class="py-16 px-4">
        <div class="blog-content">
            <p>Someone's toilet is overflowing at 11 PM. They grab their phone, Google "emergency plumber near me," and guess what? <strong>Your competitor shows up first</strong> - even though you're better, faster, and cheaper.</p>

            <p>Why? Because they fixed these 10 Google My Business mistakes and you haven't. Yet.</p>

            <p>Good news: Most of these take less than 10 minutes to fix. Bad news: every day you wait is another day your competitors are eating your lunch.</p>

            <h2>Mistake #1: Treating Your GMB Like a "Set It and Forget It" Thing</h2>

            <div class="mistake-card">
                <p class="font-bold text-red-600 mb-2">❌ What You're Doing Wrong:</p>
                <p>You set up your Google Business Profile in 2019 and haven't touched it since. Maybe you log in once a year to respond to a bad review.</p>
            </div>

            <div class="fix-card">
                <p class="font-bold text-green-700 mb-2">✅ How To Fix It:</p>
                <p>Google rewards active profiles. You should be posting at least once a week - photos of jobs, special offers, helpful tips. Takes 2 minutes. Seriously.</p>
                <p class="mt-2"><strong>Quick Win:</strong> Post a photo of a job you completed this week with a caption like "Fixed a slab leak in [Neighborhood] today. Same-day service available - call now!" Boom. You just told Google you're active AND you service that area.</p>
            </div>

            <h2>Mistake #2: Wrong Business Category</h2>

            <div class="mistake-card">
                <p class="font-bold text-red-600 mb-2">❌ What You're Doing Wrong:</p>
                <p>Your primary category is "Plumber" but you also do water heater installation, drain cleaning, and emergency repairs. You're leaving money on the table.</p>
            </div>

            <div class="fix-card">
                <p class="font-bold text-green-700 mb-2">✅ How To Fix It:</p>
                <p>Primary category should be your main service (probably "Plumber"). But add additional categories:</p>
                <ul class="mt-2 space-y-1">
                    <li>• Water heater installation service</li>
                    <li>• Drainage service</li>
                    <li>• Emergency plumber</li>
                    <li>• Plumbing supply store (if applicable)</li>
                </ul>
                <p class="mt-2">This makes you show up for way more searches without spending a dime more.</p>
            </div>

            <h2>Mistake #3: Lame Business Description</h2>

            <div class="mistake-card">
                <p class="font-bold text-red-600 mb-2">❌ What You're Doing Wrong:</p>
                <p class="italic">"We are a full-service plumbing company serving [City] since 1995. We pride ourselves on quality workmanship and customer satisfaction."</p>
                <p class="mt-2">Wow. Riveting. Just like every other plumber in town.</p>
            </div>

            <div class="fix-card">
                <p class="font-bold text-green-700 mb-2">✅ How To Fix It:</p>
                <p class="italic">"24/7 emergency plumber in [City]. We fix burst pipes, clogged drains, water heater failures, and slab leaks. Most calls answered in under 5 minutes, on-site within 90 minutes. Flat-rate pricing - no surprises."</p>
                <p class="mt-2">See the difference? Specific services, response time, and what makes you different. Use your 750 characters wisely.</p>
            </div>

            <h2>Mistake #4: No Photos (Or Terrible Ones)</h2>

            <div class="mistake-card">
                <p class="font-bold text-red-600 mb-2">❌ What You're Doing Wrong:</p>
                <p>You have 3 photos total: your logo, a blurry truck, and a stock photo of a wrench. Meanwhile your competitor has 50+ photos of actual work.</p>
            </div>

            <div class="fix-card">
                <p class="font-bold text-green-700 mb-2">✅ How To Fix It:</p>
                <p>Take your phone out on every job. Get photos of:</p>
                <ul class="mt-2 space-y-1">
                    <li>• Before and after shots</li>
                    <li>• Your truck/van on site</li>
                    <li>• Your team working</li>
                    <li>• Equipment you use</li>
                    <li>• The problem you fixed</li>
                </ul>
                <p class="mt-2">Upload 3-5 photos per week. Google loves fresh content. Plus, people trust businesses that show their actual work - not stock photos.</p>
            </div>

            <h2>Mistake #5: Ignoring Reviews (Good AND Bad)</h2>

            <div class="mistake-card">
                <p class="font-bold text-red-600 mb-2">❌ What You're Doing Wrong:</p>
                <p>You have 12 five-star reviews... and never responded to any of them. Oh, and that 1-star from 3 months ago? Still sitting there with no response.</p>
            </div>

            <div class="fix-card">
                <p class="font-bold text-green-700 mb-2">✅ How To Fix It:</p>
                <p><strong>Respond to EVERY review within 24 hours.</strong> Google tracks this.</p>
                <p class="mt-2">For 5-star reviews:</p>
                <p class="italic">"Thanks John! Glad we could get your water heater replaced the same day. We're here 24/7 if you ever need anything else!"</p>
                <p class="mt-2">For bad reviews:</p>
                <p class="italic">"We're sorry to hear about your experience. This isn't the level of service we aim for. Please call us at [number] so we can make this right."</p>
                <p class="mt-2">Pro tip: Get more reviews by texting customers a direct link after each job. "Hey, would you mind leaving us a review? Here's the link: [URL]" Gets way more responses than asking them to "find us on Google."</p>
            </div>

            <h2>Mistake #6: Wrong Service Hours</h2>

            <div class="mistake-card">
                <p class="font-bold text-red-600 mb-2">❌ What You're Doing Wrong:</p>
                <p>Your GMB says you're closed Sundays. But you do 24/7 emergency service. Someone with a burst pipe on Sunday morning just called your competitor.</p>
            </div>

            <div class="fix-card">
                <p class="font-bold text-green-700 mb-2">✅ How To Fix It:</p>
                <p>If you offer 24/7 emergency service, your hours should say "Open 24 hours." Don't list your office hours - list when customers can actually reach you.</p>
                <p class="mt-2">Use special hours for holidays when you'll be closed. Google will automatically update it.</p>
            </div>

            <h2>Mistake #7: Not Using Posts</h2>

            <div class="mistake-card">
                <p class="font-bold text-red-600 mb-2">❌ What You're Doing Wrong:</p>
                <p>You've never made a single Google Post. You're literally invisible compared to competitors who post weekly.</p>
            </div>

            <div class="fix-card">
                <p class="font-bold text-green-700 mb-2">✅ How To Fix It:</p>
                <p>Google Posts show up right on your profile. Use them for:</p>
                <ul class="mt-2 space-y-1">
                    <li>• "$50 off water heater installation this week"</li>
                    <li>• "New: Same-day drain cleaning service now available"</li>
                    <li>• "Cold weather tip: Know where your shut-off valve is!"</li>
                </ul>
                <p class="mt-2">Posts stay active for 7 days, so aim for 1 per week minimum. Takes 2 minutes on your phone.</p>
            </div>

            <h2>Mistake #8: Missing Service Areas</h2>

            <div class="mistake-card">
                <p class="font-bold text-red-600 mb-2">❌ What You're Doing Wrong:</p>
                <p>You listed your city as your service area. But you actually service 15 different neighborhoods. Google has no idea.</p>
            </div>

            <div class="fix-card">
                <p class="font-bold text-green-700 mb-2">✅ How To Fix It:</p>
                <p>Add every neighborhood, ZIP code, and nearby city you service. Be specific:</p>
                <ul class="mt-2 space-y-1">
                    <li>• Downtown Phoenix</li>
                    <li>• Scottsdale</li>
                    <li>• Tempe</li>
                    <li>• Mesa</li>
                    <li>• Gilbert</li>
                </ul>
                <p class="mt-2">The more specific you are, the more local searches you'll show up for.</p>
            </div>

            <h2>Mistake #9: No Q&A Section</h2>

            <div class="mistake-card">
                <p class="font-bold text-red-600 mb-2">❌ What You're Doing Wrong:</p>
                <p>Someone asked "Do you offer free estimates?" on your profile 6 months ago. You never answered. They called someone else.</p>
            </div>

            <div class="fix-card">
                <p class="font-bold text-green-700 mb-2">✅ How To Fix It:</p>
                <p>Monitor your Q&A section weekly. Better yet - seed it with your own questions:</p>
                <ul class="mt-2 space-y-1">
                    <li>• Q: "Do you offer 24/7 emergency service?" A: "Yes! Call [number] any time, day or night."</li>
                    <li>• Q: "What forms of payment do you accept?" A: "Cash, check, all major credit cards, and financing available."</li>
                    <li>• Q: "Do you offer free estimates?" A: "Yes, all estimates are free with no obligation."</li>
                </ul>
                <p class="mt-2">This info shows up right on your profile. Makes it easy for customers to choose you.</p>
            </div>

            <h2>Mistake #10: Not Tracking What's Working</h2>

            <div class="mistake-card">
                <p class="font-bold text-red-600 mb-2">❌ What You're Doing Wrong:</p>
                <p>You have no idea how many people find you through Google, call you from your profile, or visit your website from GMB.</p>
            </div>

            <div class="fix-card">
                <p class="font-bold text-green-700 mb-2">✅ How To Fix It:</p>
                <p>Check your GMB Insights weekly:</p>
                <ul class="mt-2 space-y-1">
                    <li>• How many views you're getting</li>
                    <li>• Which searches you show up for</li>
                    <li>• How many people called you</li>
                    <li>• How many clicked for directions</li>
                </ul>
                <p class="mt-2">If these numbers are going down, something's broken. If they're going up, keep doing what you're doing.</p>
            </div>

            <h2>The Bottom Line</h2>

            <p>Your Google Business Profile is <strong>the most important marketing tool you have as a plumber.</strong> When someone needs a plumber RIGHT NOW, they're not browsing websites - they're looking at that map pack at the top of Google.</p>

            <p>Fix these 10 mistakes and you'll:</p>
            <ul>
                <li>Show up higher in searches</li>
                <li>Get more phone calls</li>
                <li>Win more emergency jobs</li>
                <li>Stop losing customers to competitors</li>
            </ul>

            <p>Most of this takes less than an hour total to fix. The rest is just spending 10 minutes a week staying active.</p>

